Re: How To Make a Distributed BitCoin Escrow Service

Bitcointalk

2010-09-26 17:34:26 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Itʼs not implemented yet, but the network can support a transaction
   that requires two signatures.  Itʼs described here:
   [12]http://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=750.0
   Itʼs absolutely safer than a straight payment without escrow, but not
   as good as a human arbitrated escrow, assuming you trust the human
   enough.
   In this kind of escrow, a cheater canʼt win, but itʼs still possible
   for you to lose.  It at least takes away the profit motive for cheating
   you.  The seller is assured that the money is reserved for him, while
   the buyer retains the leverage that the seller hasnʼt been paid yet
   until completion.
